    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-15T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="181"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/2986: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-15T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 15, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>373. Your 665, May 15, noon. With regard to sending an aircraft carrier to carry
                    planes which have already been set up, it would not seem possible to load the
                    planes in New York as, under international law and American statute, a vessel of
                    war cannot increase its armed strength in neutral ports. However, there would
                    seem to be no difficulties if the French desired to have the planes set up in
                    the United States, flown to Canada, and thence by Allied pilots to some port on
                    the east coast of Canada, possibly Halifax, where an aircraft carrier could load
                    them.</p>
                <p>Colonel Jacquin should naturally receive immediate instructions and adequate
                    authority.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
